description: Under new laws, owners will have to prove they can keep monkeys and primates to high 'zoo-level standards' and will require a licence.

title: English sparkling wine triumphs over champagne in blind taste test
description: Sixty per cent of French wine drinkers said they preferred wine made by Chapel Down in Kent to their native Champagne during a blind test in Reims last month.

title: Judge strikes down Arkansas' ban on gender-affirming care for transgender minors
description: A judge struck down Arkansas' 2021 ban on gender-affirming care for children as unconstitutional on Tuesday, in the first ruling of its kind.

title: Everything you missed on Love Island episode sixteen
description: Love Island series ten has delivered when it comes to drama.

title: Clare Nowland: NSW Police document shows how cops deleted 'Taser' and 'knife' from press release
description: Mention of a Taser, a knife and a 95-year-old's movements were removed from the first public statement NSW Police drafted about the fatal stunning of the great-grandmother.

title: Emu chases a curious tourist at Pinnacles Cervantes in Nambung National Park Western Australia
description: In the video, the man gets up close and personal with an emu for a good photo but soon found himself chased at high speed through Nambung National Park, West Australia.

title: Cuckoos face uncertain future in Britain as global warming impacts plans to raise their young
description: Climate change is endangering cuckoos as the iconic migratory birds' body cycles can't adapt to global warming meaning they are arriving in the UK at the wrong time to breed, warns new research.

title: COVID obsessive jokes he's sleeping in tent with air filter after partner dropped precautions
description: A man has sparked hilarity after claiming he is sleeping in a tent in his garage with an air filter' after his partner dropped precautions against the virus.

title: Labour faces backlash over calls to reverse slashing of air taxes amid cost of living crisis
description: The tax cut, to be introduced permanently under the Finance Bill, means the levy on domestic flights will fall from £13 to £6.50 to support holidaymakers amid cost of living crisis

title: Sunrise host Natalie Barr's very tough question to solider
description: Sunrise host Natalie Barr has confronted a war veteran after he referred senior ADF leaders to the International Criminal Court over alleged war crimes committed in Afghanistan.

title: Sir Bernard Jenkin votes to sanction Boris Johnson over Partygate despite facing probe himself
description: Sir Bernard Jenkin voted with other MPs to approve the Privileges Committee report that condemned Boris Johnson for misleading the House of Commons over Partygate.

title: Starmer eyes dozens of House of Lords seats in attempt to ensure future Labour government agenda
description: Even though Sir Keir opposed Boris Johnson's resignation honours list and pledged to abolish the Lords, he must appoint more peers to avoid a conflict with the upper chamber.

title: Mother who lost arm and leg in tube accident becomes first to operate AI bionic arm
description: Sarah de Lagarde, who has described herself as 80 per cent human and 20 per cent robot, will soon be utilising a new £250,000 bionic arm that she says 'can give me a piece of my life back.'

title: Hunter wellies beloved by King Charles and Kate Moss goes into administration with £100m debt
description: Hunter wellies had a royal warrant from the late Queen and commanded a premium price after being made a footwear must-have by fashion icons including Princess Diana and Kate Moss.

title: Pentagon accounting error has sent an extra $6.2 BILLION to Ukraine in the last two years
description: The Pentagon said Tuesday that an accounting error meant it had overestimated the cost of weapons sent to Ukraine, creating a $6.2 billion surplus that can be used for future assistance.

title: More than 1 in 10 properties are holiday homes in some parts of the UK, census data shows
description: Cornwall is the UK's most popular destination for holiday homes, with 6,080 getaways used by 14,230 people according to census data.

title: Scottish town rocked by Godfather-style vendettas with dead deer left rotting on boat club doorstep
description: Terrified locals in West Wemyss fear they are being targeted in a vicious vendetta worthy of classic gangster movie The Godfather.

title: Vanderbilt University turns over transgender patients' medical records to Tennessee AG's office
description: Vanderbilt University Medical Center has released the records of its transgender patients to the Tennessee Attorney General in response to an investigation.
